  "content": "# UCC-1 Financing Statement: Personal Protection for Rickey Allan Howard\r\n\r\n**Filing Date:** February 3, 2026  \r\n**Filing Jurisdiction:** Georgia Secretary of State  \r\n**Filing Type:** UCC-1 Original Financing Statement  \r\n**Purpose:** Establish secured party interest in all personal property, labor, and future earnings\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## SECURED PARTY INFORMATION\r\n\r\n**Name:** Howard Jones Family Ancestral Trust  \r\n**Organization Type:** Private Irrevocable Trust  \r\n**Address:** 595 Macon Hwy Apt 35, Athens, GA 30608  \r\n**EIN:** [Trust EIN from IRS CP_575_B.pdf]  \r\n\r\n**Alternative Secured Party (if Trust rejected):**  \r\n**Name:** Rickey Allan Howard (secured party creditor)  \r\n**Address:** 595 Macon Hwy Apt 35, Athens, GA 30608  \r\n**SSN:** [Your SSN]\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## DEBTOR INFORMATION\r\n\r\n**Legal Name (All Caps):** RICKEY ALLAN HOWARD  \r\n**Address:** 595 Macon Hwy Apt 35, Athens, GA 30608  \r\n**SSN:** [Your SSN]  \r\n**Date of Birth:** [Your DOB]  \r\n**Organization Type:** Individual / Natural Person  \r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## COLLATERAL DESCRIPTION\r\n\r\nThis financing statement covers all present and future personal property of the Debtor, including but not limited to:\r\n\r\n### 1. Labor and Intellectual Capital\r\n- All labor, skills, knowledge, and expertise of RICKEY ALLAN HOWARD\r\n- All future earnings from employment, self-employment, consulting, or services\r\n- All intellectual property created by RICKEY ALLAN HOWARD (inventions, ideas, discoveries)\r\n- All copyrights, trademarks, trade secrets, and know-how\r\n\r\n### 2. Tangible Personal Property\r\n- All household goods, furniture, appliances, electronics\r\n- All vehicles (cars, motorcycles, boats, etc.)\r\n- All jewelry, watches, collectibles, art, and valuables\r\n- All tools, equipment, and machinery\r\n- All clothing, personal effects, and belongings\r\n\r\n### 3. Financial Assets\r\n- All bank accounts, savings accounts, checking accounts\r\n- All investment accounts (stocks, bonds, mutual funds, crypto)\r\n- All retirement accounts (401k, IRA, pension plans)\r\n- All insurance policies (life, health, auto, property)\r\n- All future tax refunds, rebates, and government benefits\r\n\r\n### 4. Real Property Interests\r\n- All present and future interests in real estate\r\n- All mineral rights, water rights, and natural resource rights\r\n- All easements, licenses, and rights-of-way\r\n\r\n### 5. Business Interests\r\n- All ownership interests in HJS Services LLC\r\n- All ownership interests in Odyssey-1 AI LLC\r\n- All membership units, stock certificates, and partnership interests\r\n- All future business ventures and entities\r\n\r\n### 6. Digital Assets\r\n- All cryptocurrencies, NFTs, and digital tokens\r\n- All domain names, websites, and online accounts\r\n- All social media accounts and digital profiles\r\n- All software licenses and digital subscriptions\r\n\r\n### 7. Rights and Claims\r\n- All legal claims, causes of action, and lawsuits\r\n- All contract rights and agreements\r\n- All licenses, permits, and government authorizations\r\n- All rebates, refunds, and credits\r\n\r\n### 8. Proceeds and Products\r\n- All proceeds, products, rents, and profits from the above collateral\r\n- All substitutions, replacements, and additions to the above collateral\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## LEGAL BASIS\r\n\r\nThis security interest is created pursuant to:\r\n\r\n1. **Uniform Commercial Code (UCC) Article 9** - Secured Transactions\r\n2. **Common Law Right of Self-Ownership** - Every living man/woman owns their own labor and body\r\n3. **13th Amendment to the U.S. Constitution** - Prohibition of involuntary servitude (no one can claim ownership of another's labor without consent)\r\n4. **Priority of Security Interests** - First-filed security interest has priority over later creditors\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## PURPOSE AND INTENT\r\n\r\nThe Secured Party claims a superior security interest in all collateral described above to:\r\n\r\n1. **Protect Against Future Creditors:** Establish priority over any future liens, judgments, or claims\r\n2. **Preserve Family Wealth:** Ensure RICKEY ALLAN HOWARD's labor and property benefit his family/Trust\r\n3. **Prevent Unlawful Taking:** Prevent third parties from claiming ownership of the Debtor's labor or property without proper compensation\r\n4. **Establish Public Record:** Create public notice of existing security interest (UCC-1 is public filing)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## DEBTOR ACKNOWLEDGMENT\r\n\r\nRICKEY ALLAN HOWARD acknowledges and agrees:\r\n\r\n1. The Secured Party (Howard Jones Family Ancestral Trust) has a first-priority security interest in all collateral described above\r\n2. All future earnings and property acquired by RICKEY ALLAN HOWARD are subject to this security interest\r\n3. RICKEY ALLAN HOWARD may not grant security interests to other parties without written consent of the Secured Party\r\n4. This security interest is irrevocable and perpetual (5-year UCC filing renewable indefinitely)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## FILING INSTRUCTIONS\r\n\r\n### Online Filing (Recommended)\r\n1. Go to: https://ecorp.sos.ga.gov/ucc\r\n2. Select \"File UCC-1 Financing Statement\"\r\n3. Enter Secured Party information (Trust name, address, EIN)\r\n4. Enter Debtor information (RICKEY ALLAN HOWARD, address, SSN)\r\n5. Copy/paste collateral description from Section 3 above\r\n6. Pay filing fee ($25-$50)\r\n7. Download confirmation and filing number\r\n\r\n### Paper Filing (Alternative)\r\n1. Complete Georgia UCC-1 form (available at sos.ga.gov)\r\n2. Attach collateral description (pages 1-2 of this document)\r\n3. Mail to: Georgia Superior Court Clerks' Cooperative Authority, 1875 Century Blvd NE, Suite 100, Atlanta, GA 30345\r\n4. Include check for filing fee ($25-$50)\r\n5. Wait 7-10 days for confirmation\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## POST-FILING ACTIONS\r\n\r\nAfter filing is confirmed:\r\n\r\n1. ✅ **Save Filing Confirmation:** Keep PDF copy and filing number safe\r\n2. ✅ **Record in Trust Archive:** Add to Volume 3 (Private Trust Records)\r\n3. ✅ **Notify Creditors (if needed):** If you have existing debts, send notice that collateral is subject to prior security interest\r\n4. ✅ **Renewal Reminder:** UCC-1 filings expire in 5 years - set calendar reminder to renew in January 2031\r\n5. ✅ **Update Estate Plan:** Inform attorney that personal UCC-1 filing exists\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## LEGAL DISCLAIMER\r\n\r\nThis filing is made in good faith to establish a lawful security interest under the Uniform Commercial Code. The filer acknowledges:\r\n\r\n- This filing does NOT eliminate existing legitimate debts or obligations\r\n- This filing does NOT authorize tax evasion or fraud\r\n- This filing does NOT create immunity from lawful court orders\r\n- This filing creates a PUBLIC RECORD that establishes priority of security interests\r\n\r\nThe purpose is to protect against FUTURE unlawful claims, not to avoid EXISTING legitimate obligations.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## SUPPORTING DOCUMENTS (Attach to Filing)\r\n\r\n1. Copy of Trust EIN Confirmation Letter (proves Trust is legitimate entity)\r\n2. Copy of Trustee Certificate of Authority (proves Trust has legal authority)\r\n3. This collateral description document\r\n4. Optional: Affidavit of Self-Ownership (sworn statement that you own your own labor)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Document Control:**  \r\nFile: UCC1_PERSONAL_PROTECTION_RICKEY_HOWARD.md  \r\nVersion: 1.0  \r\nDate: February 3, 2026  \r\nClassification: Confidential — For Personal Legal Protection\r\n\r\n**Filing Status:** ⏳ DRAFT — Ready to file when you decide  \r\n**Filing Fee:** $25-$50 (varies by county)  \r\n**Processing Time:** Immediate (online) or 7-10 days (paper)  \r\n**Expiration:** 5 years (renewable)\r\n"
}